rComments: I have taken 4 courses with Dr. Sturge and she is one of the best profs I have had. She made my university experience so much more interesting. I get what people say about her reading of slides but she always mentions that it helps students retain the material better. Her exams are extremely far and she is alwyas so kind and helpful. Love her!!

Goes through slides with the speed of 3 slides per minute. Someone needs to keep a Guinness record of how fast she can read of a slide. Boring and monotone and you need three espresso shots to stay awake during lectures

Lectures are extremely boring and so hard not to zone out after 5 minutes. She is mostly reading of the slides so there's no opportunity of note taking. The exams were relatively fair but lecture heavy. There are unnecessary loooong readings for each week that serve no purpose but to answer a 5 question quiz due every week.

Lectures seem heavy with a lot of information consisting mostly of examples and statistics on the slides, however they are more there for your own curiosity and to help facilitate the learning process in grasping concepts. Class participation in her lectures are both educational and representative of the types of questions which appear on exams.
Her exams are fair and the course is interesting. There is a LOT of information per lecture.
